nHere, diversity is a source of pride, even to Republicans whose party is led by anti-immigrant President Donald Trump.\r\n\n\r\n在这里，多样性是自豪的源泉，即使是由反移民总统特朗普领导的共和党人也为此而自豪。\r\n\n\r\n“Las Vegas is truly unique,” remarked West Allen, an attorney and community leader at his local Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints. “My children go to school with people from Russia, from Mexico, from China, almost anywhere in the world.”\r\n\n\r\n当地耶稣基督后期圣徒教会的律师和社区领袖艾伦说，“拉斯维加斯真的是独一无二的，我的孩子和来自俄罗斯，墨西哥，中国，几乎世界任何地方的人一起上学。”\r\n\n\r\nIn Allen’s view, immigrants enrich the country overall, and contribute to what he describes as Las Vegas’ deeply spiritual community that looks out for each other.\r\n\n\r\n在艾伦的观点中，移民丰富了整个国家，并为他所描述的拉斯维加斯深刻的精神社区做出了贡献。\r\n\n\r\n“We want people who are the best people from every nation to become Americans,” Allen said.\r\n\n\r\n艾伦说：“我们希望每个国家最优秀的人都成为美国人。”\r\n\n\r\n\nChanging population, changing votes?\r\n\n\r\n变化的人口，变化的选票？\n\r\n\n\r\n\n\r\n                   内华达州莫阿帕谷这样白人占人口92％的农村地区的居民认为，随着整体州选民变得更加多元化，移民政策将间接影响他们。\r\n                \n\r\nIn 2016, Las Vegas swung Nevada’s overall vote for Democratic candidate Hillary Clinton, while at the other end of Clark County, Moapa Valley voted 78 percent for Trump.\r\n\n\r\n2016年，拉斯维加斯推动内华达州整体投票给民主党候选人希拉里·克林顿，而在克拉克县另一端，莫阿帕谷78％的选票支持特朗普。\r\n\n\r\nLatinos helped give the state to Clinton, choosing her over Trump by a nationwide margin of 66 to 28. It was the third consecutive presidential race in which Nevada voted blue.\r\n\n\r\n拉美裔帮助克林顿赢得这个州，以66比28的选票比例选择她而非特朗普，这是内华达州连续第三次在总统选举中投票支持民主党人。\r\n\n\r\nBefore that, the state was reliably Republican, or red.\r\n\n\r\n在此之前，这个州是坚定的共和党州，或红色州。\r\n\n\r\nIn midterm election years, like this one, Nevada tends to be purple, electing a mixed bag of congressional candidates.\r\n\n\r\n在中期选举年，就像今年，内华达州往往是紫色的，选出了混合的国会候选人。\r\n\n\r\nThe changes in voting track the changes in demographics and have led to the assumption that Nevada will become a blue state.\r\n\n\r\n投票的变化反应人口统计的变化，并使人预测内华达州将成为一个蓝色州。\r\n\n\r\n\nBut will they vote?\r\n\n\r\n但他们会投票吗？\n\r\n\n\r\nLatinos are now 19 percent of Nevada’s eligible voters, according to the Pew Research Center.\r\n\n\r\n根据皮尤研究中心的数据，拉美裔人现在占内华达州选民的19％。\r\n\n\r\nIf they turn out in large numbers, Hispanics could sway the closely fought battle between incumbent Republican Senator Dean Heller and his democratic challenger, Jacky Rosen, a house member.\r\n\n\r\n如果他们大量投票，西班牙裔美国人可能会影响现任共和党参议员迪恩·海勒和他的民主党挑战者、众议员杰基·罗森之间的激战。\r\n\n\r\nYet, history says a vast majority of them may not vote at all. Hispanic participation in midterm elections, Pew says, has declined over the past decade and reached a record low in 2014, the last midterm election. Just 16 percent of Latino voters ages 18 to 35 cast a ballot, less than half the rate of Latinos aged 36 and older (36.2 percent) and nearly one-third that of white voters overall (45.8 percent).\r\n\n\r\n\n\r\n\n\r\n\n\r\n(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});\r\n\n\r\r\n然而，历史表明绝大多数人可能根本不投票。皮尤说，西班牙裔参加中期选举的人数在过去十年中有所下降，并在2014年上次中期选举中创下历史新低。只有16％的在18至35岁之间的拉美裔选民投票，不到36岁以上拉美裔选民的一半，几乎是白人选民总数的三分之一（45.8％）。\r\n\n\r\nBut there are more younger Latinos; they make up almost half of eligible Latino voters. So their lack of enthusiasm for voting has an outsize effect.\r\n\n\r\n但是还有更年轻的拉美裔人;他们几乎占有投票权的拉美裔选民的一半。因此，他们对投票缺乏热情有着巨大的影响。\r\n\n\r\nThe relative youth of Hispanics is also seen as closing the voting gap gradually.\r\n\n\r\n西班牙裔相对年轻的人也看似在逐渐缩小投票差距。\r\n\n\r\nHow the new Hispanic population will vote is also not assured. Midterm elections have shown mixed results for democratic congressional candidates among Latino and Hispanic voters.\r\n\n\r\n新的西班牙裔口如何投票无法保证。中期选举中，拉丁裔和西班牙裔选民对民主党国会候选人的投票结果不尽相同。\r\n\n\r\nRepublicans in Nevada plan to stick with moderate messaging and conservative, family-centric principles.\r\n\n\r\n内华达州的共和党人计划坚持立场和保守、以家庭为中心的原则。\r\n\n\r\n“Although the voting is different demographically, the values haven’t changed very much.” Las Vegas attorney Allen observed.\r\n\n\r\n拉斯维加斯的律师艾伦说，“虽然不同族裔投票不同，但价值观并没有太大变化”。\r\n\r\n\r\n"